query.result:
**English:**
97 To describe their forms, I no longer scatter 98 rhymes, reader, for another task constrains me, 99 so much that I cannot be generous with this one;
100 but read Ezekiel, who depicts them 101 as he saw them from the cold region 102 coming with wind and cloud and fire;
103 and as you will find them in his writings, 104 such were they here, except that, as to their wings, 105 John is with me and from him they differ.
**Sanskrit:**
